<span id="freeTextContainer7216760305186876030">I loved this trilogy , (tetralogy, since I have now found out there is a final book that just came out , only in Spanish for not , lucky for me I read Spanish too :) ) but I digress, this third book didn&apos;t feel whole for me , it felt like there were parts missing , like somebody had a 600 page book, and then edited 350 pages out of it thinking that it made sense , while all the core elements that have made me love this series are there (the cemetery of forgotten books, the gothic mystery, recurr</span>
  <span id="freeText7216760305186876030" style="display:none">I loved this trilogy , (tetralogy, since I have now found out there is a final book that just came out , only in Spanish for not , lucky for me I read Spanish too :) ) but I digress, this third book didn't feel whole for me , it felt like there were parts missing , like somebody had a 600 page book, and then edited 350 pages out of it thinking that it made sense , while all the core elements that have made me love this series are there (the cemetery of forgotten books, the gothic mystery, recurring characters and Madrid as background) the story feels rushed and without a goal in mind , it feels more to me like a transitionary book whose main goal is to gather buzz for the next book. I look forward to the next book (hopefully the end of these series) while this third book didn't satisfy me , I still highly recommend this tetralogy to anyone (the shadow of the wind, the angels game, the prisoner of heaven) and I still haven't found the name of the fourth. It is like no book out there.</span>
