<div id="review_861594631" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/861594631" />
    <a title="Maxwell" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1381728-maxwell"><img alt="Maxwell" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1613667301p2/1381728.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/861594631?book_show_action=true">Feb 21, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Maxwell" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Maxwell" href="/user/show/1381728-maxwell">Maxwell</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1381728-maxwell?shelf=translated">translated</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1381728-maxwell?shelf=owned">owned</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer861594631" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer429903464760142890"><br/>[<b>3.5 stars</b>]<br/>My thoughts about this book haven&apos;t changed at all upon re-reading it. It&apos;s definitely enjoyable if you have read both <i>The Angel&apos;s Game</i> and <i>The Shadow of the Wind</i>, and it sets up the story for the 4th book in the series, <i>The Labyrinth of the Spirits</i>. But as a standalone novel it doesn&apos;t really work. The plot is thin and it&apos;s quite a short book without much substance. I love the characters this world, but this feels like it could have been a novella or a few separate short stories. Sti</span>
  <span id="freeText429903464760142890" style="display:none"><br />[<b>3.5 stars</b>]<br />My thoughts about this book haven't changed at all upon re-reading it. It's definitely enjoyable if you have read both <i>The Angel's Game</i> and <i>The Shadow of the Wind</i>, and it sets up the story for the 4th book in the series, <i>The Labyrinth of the Spirits</i>. But as a standalone novel it doesn't really work. The plot is thin and it's quite a short book without much substance. I love the characters this world, but this feels like it could have been a novella or a few separate short stories. Still a fun re-read because I love Daniel and Fermin, but not one I'd start with when reading Ruiz Zafon's work.<br /><br /><u>Original Review</u><br />I enjoyed this book, though it was quite short. It basically just gives you backstory on characters from both <i>The Angel's Game</i> and <i>The Shadow of the Wind</i>. It did add a little conflict/plot to the series, but as a whole I felt like this book is more off an add-on than its own installment. I enjoyed Zafon's writing as always, and since I'm a big fan of both Daniel and Fermin, I liked spending more time with them. But as a whole I wouldn't have died if I never read this story. However, it's absolutely vital you don't read this one before reading the other two books in the series because it will definitely influence your view/knowledge of the other two books. Overall, short and sweet and I'm curious if there will be yet another book added to this series because it definitely ends on a sort of cliffhanger or at least with the ability to continue.</span>
  <a data-text-id="429903464760142890" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


