        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2732703397" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15897091053363409053">Translated from Spanish this is the third book in the Cemetery of Forgotten Books series. <br/><br/>I really enjoyed book one but found book two disappointing so I crept into this book, bracing myself for the worst. I&apos;m happy to say book three pulled it out of the bag, we are back on track. <br/><br/>My biggest issue with book two was that it had no relevance to the first book but book three has done a pretty good job of tying both books together and it now feels more like a series rather than companion novels. <br/><br/>Thi</span>
  <span id="freeText15897091053363409053" style="display:none">Translated from Spanish this is the third book in the Cemetery of Forgotten Books series. <br /><br />I really enjoyed book one but found book two disappointing so I crept into this book, bracing myself for the worst. I'm happy to say book three pulled it out of the bag, we are back on track. <br /><br />My biggest issue with book two was that it had no relevance to the first book but book three has done a pretty good job of tying both books together and it now feels more like a series rather than companion novels. <br /><br />This book is short and its all set up for the final 800 page monster of a book so there isn't much plot going on here but you do get more depth into the characters and detailed back stories. <br /><br />Am looking forward to the finale.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15897091053363409053" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
