<div id="review_3296872529" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3296872529" />
    <a title="Edgarr Alien Pooh" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/111745799-edgarr-alien-pooh"><img alt="Edgarr Alien Pooh" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1585112748p2/111745799.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3296872529?book_show_action=true">May 05, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Edgarr Alien Pooh" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Edgarr Alien Pooh" href="/user/show/111745799-edgarr-alien-pooh">Edgarr Alien Pooh</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781921922879" href="/book/show/15716396-the-prisoner-of-heaven">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/111745799-edgarr-alien-pooh?shelf=general-fiction">general-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3296872529" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10469845461649576963">The Prisoner of Heaven is the third volume in Ruiz Zafon&apos;s Cemetary of Forgotten Books series, at this stage, there is at least one more book. Like the previous two books, this book oozes atmosphere, the reader is taken on another scenic journey of Barcelona. But this one is a little different from the first two. In Shadow of the Wind and The Angel&apos;s Game we are introduced to the Sempere and Sons bookstore and the Cemetary of Forgotten Books. This volume returns us to the store and eventually th</span>
  <span id="freeText10469845461649576963" style="display:none">The Prisoner of Heaven is the third volume in Ruiz Zafon's Cemetary of Forgotten Books series, at this stage, there is at least one more book. Like the previous two books, this book oozes atmosphere, the reader is taken on another scenic journey of Barcelona. But this one is a little different from the first two. In Shadow of the Wind and The Angel's Game we are introduced to the Sempere and Sons bookstore and the Cemetary of Forgotten Books. This volume returns us to the store and eventually the Cemetary but it does not further the story, rather it retracts and enhances the history of the story.<br /><br />The bookstore has always had the helping hand of Fermin Romero de Torres as a loyal employee. His character has always been a major one within the four walls of the store but the overall plot of the series has followed the Sempere family. As Fermin approaches his wedding he begins to look at his life. The prisoner of Heaven, therefore, becomes mostly a historical novel of Fermin's life, following his early life up until he finds work in the bookstore and makes his lifelong friends. This completes the histories of all of the bookstore's staff.<br /><br />As I have yet to read the next book I can only guess that we need to know Fermin's history to further the story. If not, it is a very interesting history and an enjoyable read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10469845461649576963" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


