<div id="review_1272847969" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1272847969" />
    <a title="Jim Fonseca" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6743601-jim-fonseca"><img alt="Jim Fonseca" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1397669173p2/6743601.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1272847969?book_show_action=true">May 05, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jim Fonseca" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jim Fonseca" href="/user/show/6743601-jim-fonseca">Jim Fonseca</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6743601-jim-fonseca?shelf=spanish-authors">spanish-authors</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1272847969" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6273699857718324666">The author of The Shadow of the Wind and The Angel‚Äôs Game has written a sequel to those books forming a kind of trilogy. I say ‚Äúkind of‚Äù trilogy because they can be read independently of each other and in any order. In fact this most recent book mainly makes passing references to events and characters in the others. So we are back in a bookstore in Barcelona with mysterious goings-on that date back to the Spanish Civil War. The action jumps back and forth between the present (1957) and events in</span>
  <span id="freeText6273699857718324666" style="display:none">The author of The Shadow of the Wind and The Angel‚Äôs Game has written a sequel to those books forming a kind of trilogy. I say ‚Äúkind of‚Äù trilogy because they can be read independently of each other and in any order. In fact this most recent book mainly makes passing references to events and characters in the others. So we are back in a bookstore in Barcelona with mysterious goings-on that date back to the Spanish Civil War. The action jumps back and forth between the present (1957) and events in 1939 and 1940. In the present, the young boy from the earlier novels now has a wife and child; his elderly father still runs the bookstore and an assistant, an older man has a past as a prisoner during the Civil War and he knows secrets about the young man‚Äôs mother‚Äôs death that his father has not told him. It‚Äôs a pretty good read and better than The Angel‚Äôs Game, where I could not follow the plot, but not as good as the original, Shadow.<br /></span>
