<div id="review_336923729" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/336923729" />
    <a title="JanB " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/260116-janb"><img alt="JanB " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1527313486p2/260116.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/336923729?book_show_action=true">May 26, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="JanB " class="user" itemprop="url" name="JanB " href="/user/show/260116-janb">JanB </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780297868095" href="/book/show/13369595-the-prisoner-of-heaven">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer336923729" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4785398054094993147">Zafon is a master storyteller with gorgeous prose. Brilliant. My only complaint with Prisoner is I wish it had been longer because I wasn‚Äôt ready for the book to end. This is Fermin‚Äôs story, one of my favorite characters in the series. It‚Äôs more straightforward without the twists and turns in Shadow of the Wind and Angel‚Äôs Game, and it certainly whets my appetite for #4. This series is one of the few that I would consider re-reading at some point. They are books to curl up with and lose yourself</span>
  <span id="freeText4785398054094993147" style="display:none">Zafon is a master storyteller with gorgeous prose. Brilliant. My only complaint with Prisoner is I wish it had been longer because I wasn‚Äôt ready for the book to end. This is Fermin‚Äôs story, one of my favorite characters in the series. It‚Äôs more straightforward without the twists and turns in Shadow of the Wind and Angel‚Äôs Game, and it certainly whets my appetite for #4. This series is one of the few that I would consider re-reading at some point. They are books to curl up with and lose yourself in the story.<br /><br />P.S. In considering Shadow of the Wind now that it's a few years out and I've just finished the 3rd book in the series I'm going back and changing my rating to 5 stars. There are few authors who has the story-telling skill and can turn a phrase like Zafon!</span>
  <a data-text-id="4785398054094993147" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


